		<title>08THE WATCH HOUSE</title>
		<content> THE WATCH HOUSE WAS BUILT IN THE EARLY
 19TH CENTURY BECAUSE BODY             
 SNATCHERS DUG UP THE BODIES AND SOLD  
 THEM TO THE HOSPITALS.   THE HOSPITALS
 USED THEM FOR RESEARCH.   THE BODY    
 SNATCHERS USED TO SNEAK INTO          
 GRAVEYARDS AT NIGHT AND STEAL         
 NEWLY-BURIED BODIES.   THIS UPSET     
 THEIR RELATIVES WHO HIRED PEOPLE TO   
 WATCH OVER THE GRAVEYARDS TO PREVENT  
 THIS HAPPENING.   THE WATCH HOUSE WAS 
 BUILT AS A SHELTER FOR THE PERSON     
 GUARDING THE GRAVES.                  
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
